House of Representatives Committee on Navy has commended the Nigerian Navy for high level of discipline and quality projects embarked upon around their facilities. Speaking to Journalists, Chairman, house of representatives Committee on Navy Hon. Yusuf Gadji, at the Stakeholders meeting held at the Western Naval Command in Lagos, he commended the Chief of Naval Staff for his discipline and hardwork toward making Nigerian Navy topnotched. He said, ” I equally want to briefly commend the Navy family for the project we have seen on the level of the implementation and the quality of those projects is unanimous position of house of Representatives to commend the Western Naval Command and other units within the Lagos area including NAFTRAC and other departments of Nigerian Navy” “ The committee is comfortable with the level of Implementation with discipline within the Nigerian Navy Western Command as well as impression, coordination, effort and commitment” “ The Committee appreciate the Navy under the leadership Vice Admiral Ibok- Ete Ibass with his strategic commandants in this Western Naval Command for doing what they have done.”. Yusuf , emphasized that, It is all in an effort to make sure that all relevant stakeholders work together with the Nigerian Navy to ensure that they provide a safe and secured environment for maritime businesses to thrive and contribute to national development “for us as a committee, we have gone round, we have, we have seen what we are supposed to see and we have heard equally from officers of Nigerian Navy what we should hear from them *We are elected to discharge this responsibility no matter the commitment, that is what Nigerians expect from us and that’s why trust is mandated to us to represent them in the National Assembly”. He added that, on the second day engagement of the committee with Nigerian Navy, we have seen the problem of Nigerian Navy, we have seen the gap and the challenges that Nigerian Navy is facing and how the people of Nigeria will solve the problem of Nigerian Navy because National Assembly represent the Nigerian people and also the power giving to us in terms of provision of funds, yet Nigerian is facing a lot of challenges bringing from Maritime related Crime as well as normal issue of all insecurity and in the course of our engagement, we have seen the prominent role the Nigerian Navy is playing to combat Maritime Crime as well as the National insecurity this country is facing. “ For example, in one of the forth operation in Igbokoda,, from the brief the committee received is one of the areas that kidnapers feel as save haven for them and due to the strategic policy’s implementation of Nigerian Navy that axis too is becoming uncomfortable to then.”